    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-11T11:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-11T11:45:00-05:00" n="436"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1728: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-11T11:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1927—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Legation’s 38, February 9, 9 p.m. Keilhauer is now deposed [<hi rend="italic"
                        >disposed?</hi>] to grant request of Nicaragua for loan of $600,000 at 8
                    percent with security as already stated and an option of one year on purchase of
                    51 percent or more or [<hi rend="italic">of</hi>] stock in the national railroad
                    of Nicaragua for American company. Cable urgently if this agreeable to
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
